(89, '2', 'announcement', 0, 'Byunghoon Yoon', 'The 2nd Korean Cultural Heritage Day and Korean Film Screenings!', '<img src="upload/1318965797134105.jpg" alt="1318965797134105.jpg" /><div style="font-family:Verdana, Tahoma, ''돋움'', Dotum;font-size:10pt;color:rgb(59,61,60);"><div style="font-family:Verdana, Tahoma, ''돋움'', Dotum;font-size:10pt;color:rgb(59,61,60);"><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><b><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us" style="font-size:12pt;line-height:18px;"><br /></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><b><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us" style="font-size:12pt;line-height:18px;">Come to the Royal Ontario Museum toenjoy the 2<sup>nd</sup> Korean Cultural Heritage Day and the Korean FilmScreenings!</span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">The Consulate General of the Republic of Korea in Toronto will present the 2<sup>nd</sup> Korean Cultural Heritage Dayat the Royal Ontario Museum from 10:30am to 4:00pm on Saturday, November 5<sup>th</sup>,2011.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">At the main stage, you will find muchexcitement from all the beautiful Korean musical performances including bothtraditional and modern songs played with more than ten traditional Korean instruments.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Especially, this year’s heritage day willshow you the two most popular current Korean movies:</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><i>Leafie, A Hen into the Wild </i>and<i> Arrow, the Ultimate Weapon</i>, which have already been screened internationally in China and many other countries.</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><i><u><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Leafie,A Hen into the Wild </span></u></i><u><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">directed by Oh,Seong-Yoon (1:00pm – 2:30pm)</span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Attracting more than 2 million peopleduring the first 3 weeks since its release in Korea, Leafie, <i>A Hen into the Wild</i> is now to bescreened in Toronto for the first time ever. As one of the top Korean animations, this movie tells a story about a laying hen named Leafie who isdestined to live the “same old” repetitive life confined on the chicken farm.Her fate changes when she escapes from the chicken farm and hatches a duck egg.With the duckling (who believes Leafie to be his mother), Leafie goes on ajourney into the wild with her new son to find her freedom.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><i><u><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></u></i></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><i><u><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Arrow,the Ultimate Weapon </span></u></i><u><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">directed by Kim, Han-Min(3:30pm – 5:30pm)</span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Successfully drawing more than 7 millionfans at the box office since its release in Korea, this Korean action movie isset in an intense time period in Korean history. 13 years after King InjoRevolt, the Chosun Dynasty is attacked by the Chung Dynasty of China. A youngman named Na-mi leaves his demolished village to find his young sister, Ja-in,and her fiancé Su-koon, who were to wed on the very day of the attack. While onhis mission to rescue her, he is being traced by Jushinta, a fierce Chung Warrior, and his band of malicious men who are out to stop him. Na-mi has onlya day to rescue his sister before she is taken away to be a slave. When Na-mifinally finds his sister, Jushinta comes between them and a fierce battlebetween two of the finest warriors unfolds.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Bring your children or younger siblings! It’sa great opportunity to enjoy various interactive children’s activities such astraditional crafts and games for kids between 12pm and 4pm in the ROM’s Queens Park Rotunda.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">You really should come out to the ROM forthe Korean Cultural Heritage Day! Don’t miss out on any of these wonderfulactivities: Korean traditional musical performances, Korean filmscreenings<span> </span><i>Leafie, A Hen into the Wild, Arrow, the Ultimate Weapon, </i>Children’sCrafts Corner, admission to the ROM galleries, and more.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;"><span lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">For all these priceless cultural experiences, you <b>can save up to 30% offregular rates </b>by visiting <a href="ht