(108, '1089634772', 'free', 0, 'Byunghoon Yoon', 'Foreign Government Awards - Korea for graduate level students', '<blockquote style="color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:arial, sans-serif;line-height:normal;"><div><div class="gmail_quote"><b>Foreign Government Awards - Korea</b><br />Awards available for Canadians<br /><br />The Government of Korea through the National Institute for International Education Development offers scholarships to Canadians for study/research at the graduate level. These scholarships are based on reciprocal agreements between the governments of Korea and Canada.<br /><br />Application Deadline: March 7, 2012<br /><br />For more information, visit:<br /><a href="http://www.scholarships-bourses.gc.ca/scholarships-bourses/can/fga_korea-bge_coree.aspx?lang=eng&amp;view=d" style="color:rgb(17,85,204);">http://www.scholarships-bourses.gc.ca/scholarships-bourses/can/fga_korea-bge_coree.aspx?lang=eng&amp;view=d</a><br /><br /><br />Administered by the Canadian Bureau for International Education</div></div></blockquote>', '<blockquote type="cite" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.917969); "><div><div class="gmail_quote"><b>Foreign Government Awards - Korea</b><br>Awards available for Canadians<br><br>The Government of Korea through the National Institute for International&nbsp;Education Development offers scholarships to Canadians for study/research&nbsp;at the graduate level. These scholarships are based on reciprocal&nbsp;agreements&nbsp;between the governments of Korea and Canada.<br><br>Application Deadline: March 7, 2012<br><br>For more information, visit:<br><a href="http://www.scholarships-bourses.gc.ca/scholarships-bourses/can/fga_korea-bge_coree.aspx?lang=eng&amp;view=d" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); ">http://www.scholarships-<wbr>bourses.gc.ca/scholarships-<wbr>bourses/can/fga_korea-bge_<wbr>coree.aspx?lang=eng&amp;view=d</a><br><br><br>Administered by the Canadian Bureau for International Education</div></div></blockquote>', 0, '1328810394'),
(109, '1089634772', 'free', 0, 'Byunghoon Yoon', 'Korean transcription help required!!', '<div>An English speaking lawyer is looking for a person fluent in both Korean and English for a transcription work. Below is a full text of the e-mail regarding this request.</div><div><br /></div><div>Please e-mail tricia[at]asapreportingservices.com if you are interested or have any questions.</div><div><br /></div><div>================================================</div><blockquote class="webkit-indent-blockquote" style="margin:0 0 0 40px;border:none;padding:0px;"><div>Good Afternoon,</div><div><br /></div><div>Further to my telephone call, we are a court reporting agency with an</div><div>unusual request from a client.</div><div><br /></div><div>An English speaking lawyer is looking to examine a Korean speaking</div><div>witness.  Questions will be posed in English, answers will be provided in</div><div>Korean, and an interpreter will be there to facilitate communication.</div><div><br /></div><div>The lawyer is looking to receive a written transcript from this</div><div>examination that includes all the English spoken and all the Korean spoken</div><div>verbatim at the proceeding.  They are ideally looking for a Korean-English</div><div>stenographer to do this work and will pay for travel, but I am not sure if</div><div>such a person exists.  Alternatively we could even use two stenographers,</div><div>one English (which we have) and one Korean, who could do separate</div><div>transcripts.  I am not well versed in the Korean legal system though, so I</div><div>am not aware if they use stenographers in their pre-trial or court</div><div>proceedings as in some countries I know that they do not.  Therefore,</div><div>perhaps there are no Korean court reporters.</div><div><br /></div><div>As an option, we could make an audio recording of the examination and then</div><div>have someone fluent in Korean either insert the Korean into the English</div><div>transcript from the audio, or help us create a full Korean transcript</div><div>separate of the English one.  Unfortunately, we do not know of anyone who</div><div>is fluent in written Korean who could take on this work.</div><div><br /></div><div>We are looking for some assistance with this client request.  Any advice</div><div>on how best to meet the client''s needs, or referrals to persons or</div><div>organizations that could assist with creating this Korean portion of the</div><div>transcript would be extremely beneficial.</div><div><br /></div><div>If any further information is required, I am happy to answer any and all</div><div>questions.</div><div><br /></div><div>Thank you in advance for your assistance!</div><div><br /></div><div>Tricia Smith</div><div>Vice President</div><div><br /></div><div>www.asapreportingservices.com</div><div>Toll Free: 888.661.2727</div></blockquote>', '<div>An English speaking lawyer is looking for a person fluent in both Korean and English for a transcription work. Below is a full text of the e-mail regarding this request.</div><div><br></div><div>Please e-mail tricia[at]asapreportingservices.com if you are interested or have any questions.</div><div><br></div><div>================================================</div><blockquote class="webkit-indent-blockquote" style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div>Good Afternoon,</div><div><br></div><div>Further to my telephone call, we are a court reporting agency with an</div><div>unusual request from a client.</div><div><br></div><div>An English speaking lawyer is looking to examine a Korean speaking</div><div>witness. &nbsp;Questions will be posed in English, answers will be provided in</div><div>Korean, and an interpreter will be there to facilitate communication.</div><div><br></div><div>The lawyer is looking to receive a written transcript from this</div><div>examination that includes all the English spoken and all the Korean spoken</div><div>verbatim at the proceeding. &nbsp;They are ideally looking for a Korean-English</div><div>stenographer to do this work and will pay for travel, but I am not sure if</div><div>such a person exists. &nbsp;Alternatively we could even use two stenographers,</div><div>one English (which we have) and one Korean, who could do separate</div><div>transcripts. &nbsp;I am not well versed in the Korean legal system though, so I</div><div>am not aware if they use stenographers in their pre-trial or court</div><div>proceedings as in some countries I know that they do not. &nbsp;Therefore,</div><div>perhaps there are no Korean court reporters.</div><div><br></div><div>As an option, we could make an audio recording of the examination and then</div><div>have someone fluent in Korean either insert the Korean into the English</div><div>transcript from the audio, or help us create a full Korean transcript</div><div>separate of the English one. &nbsp;Unfortunately, we do not know of anyone who</div><div>is fluent in written Korean who could take on this work.</div><div><br></div><div>We are looking for some assistance with this client request. &nbsp;Any advice</div><div>on how best to meet the client''s needs, or referrals to persons or</div><div>organizations that could assist with creating this Korean portion of the</div><div>transcript would be extremely beneficial.</div><div><br></div><div>If any further information is required, I am happy to answer any and all</div><div>questions.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you in advance for your assistance!</div><div><br></div><div>Tricia Smith</div><div>Vice President</div><div><br></div><div>www.asapreportingservices.com</div><div>Toll Free: 888.661.2727</div></blockquote>', 0, '1328913508'),
