(118, '1089634772', 'announcement', 0, 'Byunghoon Yoon', '2012 KOFST Young Generation Forum - Application Available!', '<span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse:collapse;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:arial, sans-serif;line-height:normal;"></span><div><div>The Korea Federation of Science and Technology Societies (KOFST) is hosting 2012 Young Generation Forum (YG Forum) from July 2nd to 7th in Seoul, Korea.</div><div><br /></div><div>Each year, the YG Forum program brings young Korean heritage students/researchers from all over the world. 120 young generation participants (including 40 from Korea) will have a valuable opportunity to meet together, share their experience/knowledge, and create a world-wide network. </div><div><br /></div><div>The Association of Korean-Canadian Scientists and Engineers will send <b>12 delegates</b> from Canada to YG Forum in this year. All travel/local expenses (including airfare, accommodation, and meals) will be covered by KOFST. </div><div><br /></div></div><div>============================================================</div><div>Detailed information is as follows:</div><div><br /></div><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse:collapse;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-family:arial, sans-serif;line-height:normal;"></span><div>1.Eligibility Requirements</div><div><br /></div><div> The applicant must meet ALL requirements below:</div><div>- 1.5 or 2nd generation Korean-Canadian [born in Canada or have attended schools in Canada at least for 6 years (including high school)] </div><div>- Canadian citizen or Permanent resident</div><div>- Born after 1978</div><div>- Student Status at the Time of Application (Junior/Senior in College, Graduate student, or Postdoctoral fellow)  </div><div>- Major in Science and Engineering (including medical, medicine, and nursing) </div><div>- Ability to communicate effectively in English and Korean</div><div>- Must NOT have attended previous YG Forums</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>2. <font color="#ff2700">Application Deadline: March 20, 2012 </font> (Application package should be submitted electronically by this date) </div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>3. How to Apply</div><div><br /></div><div>a) Application documents </div><div>- Application form (Attached in this announcement or can be download from AKCSE website <a href="http://www.akcse.org/" style="color:rgb(17,85,204);">http://www.akcse.org</a>)</div><div>- Scanned copy of Canadian Passport or Permanent Resident Card as proof</div><div>- Most recent transcript (Important Note: The applicant should convert GPA in his/her transcript to % and this GPA in % should be given in the application form). </div><div>- The applicant should arrange one recommendation letter (AKCSE Chapter president, Job supervisor, Graduate supervisor, Course instructor, or Professor).</div><div><br /></div><div>b) Submit the application documents (highly recommend to consolidate all materials into one zip file) to YG Committee Chair (<a href="mailto:gapsoo.chang@usask.ca" style="color:rgb(17,85,204);">gapsoo.chang@usask.ca</a> or <a href="mailto:gapsoo.chang@gmail.com" style="color:rgb(17,85,204);">gapsoo.chang@gmail.com</a>).  </div><div>AKCSE YG Committee will not accept any incomplete or delayed applications. </div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>c) Finalist Nomination from AKCSE to KOFST on March 31, 2012</div><div><br /></div><div>d) Final Notification from KOFST: TBA</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>Attachments:</div><div><a href="http://ksac.ca/include/download.php?n=1331858267966675&amp;e=doc"><u>_YGF Application Form (doc)_</u></a></div><div><a href="http://ksac.ca/include/download.php?n=1331858321740352&amp;e=docx"><u>_YGF Selection Guidelines (docx)_</u></a></div>', '<span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: collapse; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; "><div><div>The Korea Federation of Science and Technology Societies (KOFST) is hosting 2012 Young Generation Forum (YG Forum) from July 2nd to 7th in Seoul, Korea.</div><div><br></div><div>Each year, the YG Forum program brings young Korean heritage students/researchers from all over the world. 120 young generation participants (including 40 from Korea) will have a valuable opportunity to meet together, share their experience/knowledge, and create a world-wide network.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The Association of Korean-Canadian Scientists and Engineers will send <b>12 delegates</b> from Canada to YG Forum in this year. All travel/local expenses (including airfare, accommodation, and meals) will be covered by KOFST.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div></div><div>============================================================</div><div>Detailed information is as follows:</div><div><br></div></span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-collapse: collapse; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; "><div>1.Eligibility Requirements</div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;The applicant must meet ALL requirements below:</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- 1.5 or 2nd generation Korean-Canadian [born in Canada or have attended schools in Canada at least for 6 years (including high school)]&nbsp;</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Canadian citizen or Permanent resident</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Born after 1978</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Student Status at the Time of Application (Junior/Senior in College, Graduate student, or Postdoctoral fellow) &nbsp;</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Major in Science and Engineering (including medical, medicine, and nursing)&nbsp;</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Ability to communicate effectively in English and Korean</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Must NOT have attended previous YG Forums</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>2.&nbsp;<font color="#ff2700">Application Deadline: March 20, 2012&nbsp;</font>&nbsp;(Application package should be submitted electronically by this date)&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>3. How to Apply</div><div><br></div><div>a) Application documents&nbsp;</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Application form (Attached in this announcement or can be download from AKCSE website&nbsp;<a href="http://www.akcse.org/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); ">http://www.akcse.org</a>)</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Scanned copy of Canadian Passport or Permanent Resident Card as proof</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- Most recent transcript (Important Note: The applicant should convert GPA in his/her transcript to % and this GPA in % should be given in the application form).&nbsp;</div><div><span style="white-space: pre-wrap; "> </span>- The applicant should arrange one recommendation letter (AKCSE Chapter president, Job supervisor, Graduate supervisor, Course instructor, or Professor).</div><div><br></div><div>b) Submit the application documents (highly recommend to consolidate all materials into one zip file) to YG Committee Chair (<a href="mailto:gapsoo.chang@usask.ca" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); ">gapsoo.chang@usask.ca</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="mailto:gapsoo.chang@gmail.com" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); ">gaps<wbr>oo.chang@gmail.com</a>). &nbsp;</div><div>AKCSE YG Committee will not accept any incomplete or delayed applications.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>c) Finalist Nomination from AKCSE to KOFST on March 31, 2012</div><div><br></div><div>d) Final Notification from KOFST: TBA</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Attachments:</div><div><a href="http://ksac.ca/include/download.php?n=1331858267966675&amp;e=doc"><u>_YGF Application Form (doc)_</u></a></div><div><a href="http://k